INSERT INTO `news` VALUES (2,'Peace FM Report on ARIS Samsung Room','2014-november-peace-fm-report-on-aris-samsung-room','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2014/december/peace-fm-feature.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"470\" height=\"264\" /></p><p>Technology giant, Samsung Electronics West Africa (SEWA) has introduced its first Samsung School education solution to the Al Rayan International School, East-Legon.</p><p>The solution integrates an array of Samsung devices with interactive software to impart knowledge in students. Components of the Samsung School solution are Samsung-powered e-boards, server, Samsung tablets, wifi access point and a wifi printer</p><p><a href=\"http://news.peacefmonline.com/pages/tech/201412/224983.php\">Read the rest</a></p>','Technology giant, Samsung Electronics West Africa (SEWA) has introduced its first Samsung School education solution to the Al Rayan International School, East-Legon.The solution integrates an array of Samsung devices wit...','2014-11-19 18:57:24','2015-02-21 18:51:17','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2014-12-08 00:00:00'),(3,'Samsung Smart School in ARIS','2014-november-samsung-smart-school-in-aris','/img/uploads/2014/november/akwaba-annette-austin.jpg','<p>A video report on ARIS being the first school in Ghana to implement the Samsung Smart School platform</p><div class=\"videoWrapper\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wi6NFVl6UK8\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>','A video report on ARIS being the first school in Ghana to implement the Samsung Smart School platform','2014-11-19 18:59:58','2015-02-10 21:17:54','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2014-12-10 00:00:00'),(15,'What are the beliefs and values that drive the PYP ?','2015-february-what-are-the-beliefs-and-values-that-drive-the-pyp','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/values-beliefs.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"431\" height=\"281\" /></p><p>In the PYP, it is believed that learning takes place best when it is connected to what is genuinely a component of the world around the student, not merely what is all too often contrived and then im- posed upon the student in school; that the acquisition of knowledge and skills and the search for meaning and understanding are best done in the context of the exploration of relevant content. PYP schools should provide students with learning experiences that are engaging, relevant, challenging and significant, in learning environments that are stimulating and provocative, where:</p><ul><li>adults are sensitive facilitators of the process of empowering students to value their learning and to take responsibility for it</li><li>students are seen as competent and are listened to</li><li>students are encouraged to be curious, be inquisitive, ask questions, explore and interact with the environment physically, socially and intellectually</li><li>explicit learning outcomes and the learning process are made transparent to the students</li><li>students are supported in their struggle for mastery and control on their journey to become in- dependent, autonomous learners</li><li>the learning experiences are differentiated to accommodate the range of abilities and learning styles in the group</li><li>the collaboration on the part of all the PYP teachers is high, and there is a commitment to the transdisciplinary model at the core of this programme of international education.</li></ul>','In the PYP, it is believed that learning takes place best when it is connected to what is genuinely a component of the world around the student, not merely what is all too often contrived and then im- posed upon the stud...','2015-02-07 12:40:02','2015-02-21 18:50:38','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-01-07 00:00:00'),(16,'Black Holes, an ASG Research Project','2015-february-black-holes-an-asg-research-project','','<p>Al-Rayan students Mouayad Toutoung (Year 11) and Bashhar Byrouthy (Year 10) produced a stirring video animation about the weird and wonderful topic of Black Holes! As members of the ASG (Astronomical Society of Ghana) the students meet monthly with other members to research and learn about Astronomy topics, and follow with a fruitful discussion. The meetings are held monthly at the <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/ghanaplanetarium\">Ghana Planetarium</a>.</p><p><iframe src=\"//www.youtube.com/embed/T9nArucCJzc\" width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>','Al-Rayan students Mouayad Toutoung (Year 11) and Bashhar Byrouthy (Year 10) produced a stirring video animation about the weird and wonderful topic of Black Holes! As members of the ASG (Astronomical Society of Ghana) th...','2015-02-07 12:41:30','2015-03-20 10:33:38','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-01-07 00:00:00'),(17,'Lincoln CAS trips with students from ARIS','2015-february-lincoln-cas-trips-with-students-from-aris','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2014/december/lcs_aris_cover.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"471\" height=\"278\" /></p><p>The LCS CAS program has taken service learning to another level by engaging a fellow IB school in Ghana on their CAS trips. The new initiative connects students from the two schools in joint CAS trips and encourages them to fundraise together towards a common goal.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"http://www.lincoln.edu.gh/page.cfm?p=487&amp;newsid=911\">Read the rest</a></p>','The LCS CAS program has taken service learning to another level by engaging a fellow IB school in Ghana on their CAS trips. The new initiative connects students from the two schools in joint CAS trips and encourages them...','2015-02-10 21:24:16','2015-02-21 18:50:56','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2014-12-12 00:00:00'),(18,'Accepting Disability: The School That Made All The Difference','2015-february-accepting-disability-the-school-that-made-all-the-difference','','<p><em><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/january/modern_ghana_logo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"219\" height=\"114\" /></em></p><p><em>Modern Ghana</em> reports:</p><p>No institution worth its sort would turn a blind eye to a very compelling social responsibility which, hitherto, has been neglected or forgotten for the want of a softer statement to aptly put it. However, it is quite obfuscating to find out how apathetic society is towards the physically challenged and that is easily read in the general lack of provisions made in all aspects of life.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.modernghana.com/news/591052/1/accepting-disability-the-school-that-made-all-the-.html\">Read the rest</a></p>','Modern Ghana reports:No institution worth its sort would turn a blind eye to a very compelling social responsibility which, hitherto, has been neglected or forgotten for the want of a softer statement to aptly put it. Ho...','2015-02-10 21:27:29','2015-02-21 18:50:18','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-01-09 00:00:00'),(19,'â€‹LCS collaborates with ARIS and National Forestry Commission to preserve wildlife','2015-february-lcs-collaborates-with-aris-and-national-forestry-commission-to-preserve-wildlife','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/january/aris_linconln_collaboration.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>LCS teachers, Barbara Bilgre and Eric Boateng, are spearheading a wildlife and environmental preservation project with their students in collaboration with the Forestry Commission of Ghana and Al Rayyan International School (ARIS), another IB school in Accra.</p><p>LCS CAS students will be partnering with ARIS CAS students on this community development project for the Solo Monkey Forest, as well as on smaller service projects.</p><p>Students from the two schools met at ARIS premises in East Legon for their first meeting to discuss the proposed monkey sanctuary initiative.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.lincoln.edu.gh/page.cfm?p=487&amp;newsid=934&amp;ncat=3\">Read the rest</a></p>','LCS teachers, Barbara Bilgre and Eric Boateng, are spearheading a wildlife and environmental preservation project with their students in collaboration with the Forestry Commission of Ghana and Al Rayyan International Sch...','2015-02-10 21:40:22','2015-02-21 18:50:03','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-01-30 00:00:00'),(20,'PYP Unit of Inquiry Goes to Silver Star Automotives ','2015-february-pyp-unit-of-inquiry-goes-to-silver-star-automotives','','<h3>Year One pupils took several exciting trips in connection to their Unit of Inquiry; How We Organize Ourselves. The focus was on transportation, and how it relates to the needs of a community. The inquiry took them from land, to sea, and finally air; looking at how transportation moves people and cargo.<img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/mercedes-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />The Year One pupils started their trip by bus to Silver Star Motors. Once they arrived at Silver Star, they acquainted themselves with the various vehicle models. The pupils were given V.I.P. treatment with a video presentation featuring the process of making Mercedes Benz cars and trucks. After the video, the pupils toured the showroom, exploring the Mercedes Benz, inside and out. &nbsp;&nbsp;</h3><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/mercedes-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />The Year One pupils boarded the bus and moved across town to the airport, identifying the planes that were being used to carry people, and special planes used only to move cargo.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/wara-malek.png\" alt=\"\" /><br />Another important need of a community is emergency services. The West African Rescue Association (WARA) was called for the task. The WARA Paramedic opened his Ambulance and let the excited inquirers tour the ambulance and inspect the different types of emergency response equipment all of the pupils had questions.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/february/mercedes-4.png\" alt=\"\" /><br />The unit provided the pupils with a solid grounding for inquiring into the many types of transport communities develop and how the needs of a community can influence the mode of transport within the community.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','Year One pupils took several exciting trips in connection to their Unit of Inquiry; How We Organize Ourselves. The focus was on transportation, and how it relates to the needs of a community. The inquiry took them from l...','2015-02-13 19:35:32','2015-04-08 13:09:14','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-02-13 00:00:00'),(31,'Cathryn Berger Kaye Service Learning Workshop ','2015-april-cathryn-berger-kaye-service-learning-workshop','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/LCS%20Service%20Learning/service%20learning.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Madame Dhalia (CAS Coordinator) and Mr. Brew (Humanities and Social Sciences) took part in the two day Service Learning Workshop given by the international speaker Cathryn Berger Kaye, she is also the author of T<em>he Complete Guide to Service Learning: Proven, Practical Ways to Engage Students in Civic Responsibility, Academic Curriculum, &amp; Social Action. </em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Service Learning Workshop, held at LCS was described as an insightful two days. Service learning allows students to implement skills at liberty with an extensive benefit on society. It helps to address current issues through research and problem-solving. Students have the opportunity to become better learners as they reflect on work done after activities connected to service learning to help them improve if need be.</p>\r\n<p>Ms. Kaye&rsquo;s workshops focused on fostering a culture of service, facilitating action and incorporating civic responsibility into the curriculum. Discussions focused on the need for a shift from&nbsp;<em>community service</em>, to the&nbsp;<em>service learning approach</em>&nbsp;which integrates meaningful community service with instruction to enrich the learning experience, teach civic responsibility and strengthen communities.</p>','Madame Dhalia (CAS Coordinator) and Mr. Brew (Humanities and Social Sciences) took part in the two day Service Learning Workshop given by the international speaker Cathryn Berger Kaye, she is also the author of The Compl...','2015-04-08 11:48:13','2015-04-08 11:48:13','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-01-24 00:00:00'),(21,'Ghana\'s Independence Day in ARIS','2015-march-ghanas-independence-day-in-aris','','<p class=\"p1\">Independence Day Celebrations in ARIS saw an array of colourful activities. A day when the entire school rose above personal interests to put Ghana first and celebrate an achievement, which distinguished our motherland 58 years ago. It all started with an enthralling presentation themed, &ldquo;Ghana&rsquo;s Journey to Independence&rdquo; during morning assembly, which offered students the opportunity to find out about events that transpired during the colonial rule in Ghana&rsquo;s history.</p><p class=\"p1\"><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/ghana_day/ghana_day_07.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p class=\"p2\">Students of all nationalities were elegantly dressed in Ghanaian traditional clothing to symbolise the preservation of the rich Ghanaian culture in our school and to remember the struggles of our forefathers and their relentless efforts that have made it possible to celebrate this important day.</p><p class=\"p2\"><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/ghana_day/ghana_day_02.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p class=\"p2\"><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/ghana_day/ghana_day_08.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p class=\"p2\">&ldquo;Ghana&rdquo; was the talk of the day through teaching, classroom and break-time discussions while merriments continued through out the day with an abundance of picture-taking and story-telling as we braced for a week-long celebration.</p><p class=\"p2\">FROM ARIS, WE SAY &ldquo;AYEKOO GHANA&rdquo; !</p><p class=\"p2\"><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/ghana_day/ghana_day_05.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p class=\"p2\">&nbsp;</p><p class=\"p2\"><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/ghana_day/ghana_day_04.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p class=\"p2\"><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/ghana_day/ghana_day_09.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Independence Day Celebrations in ARIS saw an array of colourful activities. A day when the entire school rose above personal interests to put Ghana first and celebrate an achievement, which distinguished our motherland 5...','2015-03-06 20:32:08','2015-03-18 08:42:01','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-03-06 00:00:00'),(22,'Celebrating Pi Day!','2015-march-celebrating-pi-day','','<p>In what many consider the highlight of the year, ARIS Secondary school students celebrated <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pi_Day\">international Pi Day</a>&nbsp;with their teachers.&nbsp;If one day of the year screams &ldquo;Party&rdquo; in our school, that day is March 14. Each year, the Mathematics Department gathers a collection of ideas and activities that will help plan the Pi Day from all Departments, and the school takes a break from the normal routine to celebrate Pi.</p><p>The event included Pi-ing teachers, word games and field activities with items that have circle shapes (Cakes, Doughnuts, hoops..) The money raised went to the math department for research and getting more resources.</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/pi%20day/pi_day_05.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/pi%20day/pi_day_08.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>This year&rsquo;s Pi Day is not an ordinary one. It is in fact, an epic Pi Day on 3.14.15 at 9.26.53. This date and time corresponds to the first 10 digits of Pi (&pi; = 3.141592653). Incidentally, this happens once every century, which makes this one truly a once-in-a-lifetime event. The next Pi Day will be in 100 years.</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/pi%20day/pi_day_09.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/pi%20day/pi_day_10.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>Pi has a gazillion-and-one uses in everyday life. Therefore, the events are planned to engage our pupils and the community in the fun of experimental learning as a way to inspire the next generation of scientists, researchers, medical practitioners and educators who will drive life changing innovation. It is used to calculate the circumferences and areas of circle, and has many applications in Physics, Engineering, Genetics, Ecological changes and Global Warming. But it appears &lsquo;behind the scenes&rsquo; in just countless ways across many disciplines.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>','In what many consider the highlight of the year, ARIS Secondary school students celebrated international Pi Day&nbsp;with their teachers.&nbsp;If one day of the year screams &ldquo;Party&rdquo; in our school, that day is...','2015-03-14 09:08:06','2015-03-20 08:45:50','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-03-14 00:00:00'),(23,'ARIS Wins Fun Run','2015-march-aris-wins-fun-run','','<p>A few hundred people took part in the fifth edition of the Family Fun Run event organised by Happy Fm and Lakeside Marina, in Accra. The Family Fun Run is a family event held annually on Independence Day to encourage healthy living.<br />Family Fun Run participants met their match, running against a team of ARIS Secondary Students (Mouayad Toutoungi, Omar Farouk, Bashhar Byrouthy, Karim Beiruti, Hauwa Ibrahim Aminu. The students arrived in Medina at 5:30 am ready to run the grueling six-kilometers.</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/fun%20run/fun_run_2015.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>The runners were proud of the outcome, taking home the trophy for Fastest School in the 13 &ndash; 18 age category. The team also won a Cannon printer/copier for ARIS. &nbsp;</p>','A few hundred people took part in the fifth edition of the Family Fun Run event organised by Happy Fm and Lakeside Marina, in Accra. The Family Fun Run is a family event held annually on Independence Day to encourage hea...','2015-03-18 08:56:51','2015-03-18 10:31:39','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-03-18 00:00:00'),(26,'CAS Solo Monkey Sanctuary Trip ','2015-march-cas-solo-monkey-sanctuary-trip','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Zoo/SAM_0093.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />The Solo Forest Monkey Sanctuary is one hour from ARIS in Old Bortianor, the Kokrobite Area. The area is not only covered with Wawa, Odum and Sapele Mohagany trees but is home to approximately 70 Mona and Spot Nosed monkeys, butterflies, birds and reptiles. The Solo Spring originates from a nearby highland and runs through the forest which gathers in a pool and serves as the main source of water for the inhabitants. Under law poachers are prohibited to hunt. The 30 acre sanctuary is under tremendous threat from real estate encroachers.&nbsp;<img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Zoo/054.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />ARIS students from Year 7-11 and a few friends from LCS, along with the guide are fighting to save the animals and the remaining 30 acres of the 100 acres, as well as, create awareness about environmental issues in the area and throughout Ghana. On this particular trip, students engaged in tree planting, a cleanup of surrounding areas and construction of two simple footbridges across the natural stream.</p>','The Solo Forest Monkey Sanctuary is one hour from ARIS in Old Bortianor, the Kokrobite Area. The area is not only covered with Wawa, Odum and Sapele Mohagany trees but is home to approximately 70 Mona and Spot Nosed monk...','2015-03-20 10:19:00','2015-04-06 12:01:20','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2014-11-22 00:00:00'),(25,'Inquiry and the School Librarian','2015-march-inquiry-and-the-school-librarian','','<p>ARIS librarian Katie, recently had the opportunity to go participate in an IB Librarian training at the AISA Conference in early March of 2015. This was an incredible opportunity to meet and collaborate with other librarians in Africa along with it being set in beautiful Cape Town, South Africa. The three day conference was packed with interactive sessions with the facilitator Dawn Rutland, who is a certified IB trainer at St. Johns International School in Waterloo, Belgium.</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/Inquiry%20and%20the%20school%20librarian/IMG_20150307_151412458.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>Many topics were covered, a few included: cycle of inquiry, academic honesty, library resources, OPACs, e-book platforms, and the learner profile. Katie found the workshop unique in the way that it spanned the three IB Programmes and had a big emphasis on international resources for students around the world. Katie gained a sense that many of concepts in the IB overlapped in the area of international mindedness. Culminating projects, Mother tongue resources, multiple language courses, made it clear that the IB Programme is striving for a way of exploring, researching, and looking at the world in a way that other school programmes do not.</p><p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/Inquiry%20and%20the%20school%20librarian/IMG_20150307_151447311.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>Katie was endeared to Dawn and the two other women in her training for being open minded, kind, and honest about the obstacles that librarians have. The training emphasized the importance of having face-to-face conversations with other librarians who can understand and help each other over the hurdles. Katie hopes she can give to ARIS what Dawn and AISA gave to her, which is the opportunity to be a teacher and learner at the same time.</p>','ARIS librarian Katie, recently had the opportunity to go participate in an IB Librarian training at the AISA Conference in early March of 2015. This was an incredible opportunity to meet and collaborate with other librar...','2015-03-20 10:07:11','2015-03-21 11:52:03','news','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','2015-03-20 00:00:00'),(27,'Teaching and Learning through Inquiry Workshop','2015-march-teaching-and-learning-through-inquiry-workshop','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/Inquiry%20and%20the%20school%20librarian/IMG-20150327-WA0004.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />ARIS Primary Teachers enjoyed an exciting and engaging In-School Workshop on Teaching and Learning through Inquiry, by Lucy Elliott. <br />The workshop focused on 21st Century Teaching and Learning through Inquiry. Inquiry-based Learning describes a process of educational discovery, wherein a student is guided to \"see\" issues, ask meaningful questions, and then decide how to answer those questions. <br /><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/Inquiry%20and%20the%20school%20librarian/IMG-20150306-WA0025.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />The workshop highlighted Kath Murdoch and Kathy Short Inquiry Cycles, as well as the techniques, strategies, and activities that should take place in Inquiry settings. These strategies will enable pupils to become independent learners with a curiosity that goes beyond information and experience, to seek explanations. The workshop concluded by challenging the ARIS Teachers to create engaging Inquiry-based Learning projects in their own classrooms.</p>','ARIS Primary Teachers enjoyed an exciting and engaging In-School Workshop on Teaching and Learning through Inquiry, by Lucy Elliott. The workshop focused on 21st Century Teaching and Learning through Inquiry. Inquiry-bas...','2015-03-20 10:51:22','2015-04-06 21:33:12','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-03-07 00:00:00'),(28,'CAS Cocoa Farm Trip','2015-march-cas-cocoa-farm-trip','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Zoo/Cocoa.JPG\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>ARIS Year 10 and 11 students engaged in their first service learning project by supporting cocoa farmers in the village of Apono apono near Suhum, which is located two hours north of Accra &ndash; Kumasi route.<img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Zoo/cocoa.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Students supported free trade cocoa farmers by engaging in a variety of farming activities involved in organic cocoa farming. Students learned techniques such as weeding, plucking cocoa, harvesting, scooping out raw beans, the fermentation and drying beans process. <img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Zoo/cocoa5.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Major aspects of this experiential learning trip was interacting and immersing themselves with rural folks and farmers, learning about survival skills of forest living and the value of hard work.&nbsp;</p>','ARIS Year 10 and 11 students engaged in their first service learning project by supporting cocoa farmers in the village of Apono apono near Suhum, which is located two hours north of Accra &ndash; Kumasi route.Students s...','2015-03-30 11:01:23','2015-04-06 11:41:14','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2014-11-08 00:00:00'),(29,'CAS Accra Zoo Clean Up ','2015-march-cas-accra-zoo-clean-up','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Zoo/CAS%20ZOO.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />The Accra Zoo is home to monkeys, antelopes, butterflies, birds, reptiles and several other animals. ARIS students supported Zookeepers with routine clean up, animal care and educational tours.<br /><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Zoo/SAM_1623.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />The Students hope to support future conservation action through engaging in frequent developmental volunteer opportunities. The CAS volunteer development programmes are designed to be fun and educational while building skills and inspiring ARIS youth to appreciate, care for, and conserve nature.<br /><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Zoo/SAM_1596.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p>','The Accra Zoo is home to monkeys, antelopes, butterflies, birds, reptiles and several other animals. ARIS students supported Zookeepers with routine clean up, animal care and educational tours.The Students hope to suppor...','2015-03-30 11:49:08','2015-04-06 11:06:47','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-03-30 00:00:00'),(30,'CAS Trinity Academy Library Project','2015-march-cas-trinity-academy-library-project','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Library%20Trinity%20School/SAM_2754.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Trinity Academy is a nonprofit charity based local Ghanaian school in Dome, Accra. Over the course of 20 years, a majority of funding for building and educational resources are either fund raised or donated. Most students attending Trinity Academy are improvised and unable to pay termly school fees which are as low as GHC 200. Trinity Academy has an open door policy and does not discriminate based on economic status. Their main goal is to educate all children to the best of their ability. Despite the lack of modern resources and facilities, Admin and Teachers are dedicated and persevering.<img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Library%20Trinity%20School/SAM_2579.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />On Saturday March 14th 2015 from 7 a.m. until 4 p.m, students from the ARIS Social Welfare Group, supported by friends and the Art Department engaged in a service learning project to help set up the library. The ARIS Social Welfare Club collected close to 400 books for the project.&nbsp;<br /><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Library%20Trinity%20School/SAM_2567.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p><p>Students were able to reconstruct, polish and paint shelves, tables and benches and paint the library. Students wrote educational quotes on walls, stamped books with the school logo, categorized books, set up each book for check out and set up individual books in the library for check out. Book collections and ongoing work will continue in an effort to develop the library. <br /><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/CAS%20Library%20Trinity%20School/IMG_0609.jpg\" alt=\"\" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>','Trinity Academy is a nonprofit charity based local Ghanaian school in Dome, Accra. Over the course of 20 years, a majority of funding for building and educational resources are either fund raised or donated. Most student...','2015-03-30 11:58:46','2015-04-06 12:53:52','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-03-14 00:00:00'),(32,'Parents Meeting-What Is An IB Education?','2015-april-parents-meeting-what-is-an-ib-education','','<p>At the monthly IBDP parents/students meeting, Mr. Trumper took the parents/students through a detailed presentation, outlining the International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme. The parents learned more about the IB philosophy and the value of the IB Programme.</p><p>Parents were given a pre-meeting reading assignment, taken from the IBO website titled: What is an IB Education? <a href=\"http://www.ibo.org/globalassets/publications/what-is-an-ib-education-en.pdf\">http://www.ibo.org/globalassets/publications/what-is-an-ib-education-en.pdf</a>&nbsp;</p>','At the monthly IBDP parents/students meeting, Mr. Trumper took the parents/students through a detailed presentation, outlining the International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme. The parents learned more about the IB phil...','2015-04-08 12:22:22','2015-04-08 12:36:07','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2014-11-12 00:00:00'),(33,'Parents Meeting-IBDP/CAS','2015-april-parents-meeting-ibdpcas','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/Parents%20Meetings/Al-RayanWebsiteShoot-21.01.15-10462.jpg\" alt=\"CAS Parents Meeting \" /><br />Many Secondary Level 2 parents came out today for the monthly IBDP parents meeting, topic: IBDP/CAS. The International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme CAS parent meeting was delivered by Mr. Trumper (Head of Secondary) and Madame Dhalia (Counselor/CAS Coordinator). Parents/students came prepared to ask questions and learn more about CAS and the value of the International Baccalaureate Programme (IBDP).&nbsp;</p>','Many Secondary Level 2 parents came out today for the monthly IBDP parents meeting, topic: IBDP/CAS. The International Baccalaureate Diploma Programme CAS parent meeting was delivered by Mr. Trumper (Head of Secondary) a...','2015-04-08 12:55:46','2015-04-08 13:02:25','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-01-21 00:00:00'),(34,'Parents Meeting-IBDP/TOK','2015-april-parents-meeting-ibdptok','','<p>The Theory of Knowledge (TOK) is one of the three elements that make up the core of the Diploma Programme, it sits alongside the Extended Essay and CAS. The TOK is designed to develop a coherent approach to learning, it unifies the academic area and encourages appreciation of other cultural perspectives.</p>\r\n<p>The TOK Course \"Challenges students and their teachers to think critically on different ways of knowing and areas of knowledge, and to consider the role knowledge plays in our society. TOK encourages students to become aware of themselves as thinkers to become aware of the complexity of knowledge and to recognize the need to act responsibility in their society and the world.\"</p>\r\n<p>The meeting covered all aspects of TOK, if you missed any part of this parent meeting, please email Mr. Brew. </p>','The Theory of Knowledge (TOK) is one of the three elements that make up the core of the Diploma Programme, it sits alongside the Extended Essay and CAS. The TOK is designed to develop a coherent approach to learning, it...','2015-04-08 14:00:09','2015-04-08 14:00:09','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-02-25 00:00:00'),(35,'Parents Meeting-IBDP Extended Essay ','2015-april-parents-meeting-ibdp-extended-essay','','<p>The extended essay is a required component of the International Baccalaureate&reg; (IB) Diploma Programme (DP). It is an independent, self-directed piece of research, finishing with a 4,000-word paper.</p><p>The extended essay provides:practical preparation for undergraduate research, an opportunity for students to investigate a topic of special interest to them, which is also related to one of the student\'s six DP subjects.</p><p>An extended essay can also be undertaken in world studies, where students carry out an in-depth interdisciplinary study of an issue of contemporary global significance, across two IB diploma disciplines. -Taken from the IBO.ORG website.</p><p>The extended essay parent meeting covered all aspects of the extended essay. The parents and students learned the significance of the extended essay, how it is structured and assessed.</p><p>If you missed this meeting, please email Mr. Trumper (Head of Secondary) for the PowerPoint presentation.</p>','The extended essay is a required component of the International Baccalaureate&reg; (IB) Diploma Programme (DP). It is an independent, self-directed piece of research, finishing with a 4,000-word paper.The extended essay...','2015-04-08 14:23:58','2015-04-08 14:31:21','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-03-25 00:00:00'),(36,'PYP There\'s Only One You - Who We Are','2015-april-pyp-theres-only-one-you-who-we-are','','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/news/2015/march/Only%20One%20You/SAM_2163.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />In the book There\'s Only One You, Adri\'s mama and papa share some of the wisdom they have gained through the years with their eager son. Their words, simple and powerful, are meant to comfort and guide him as he goes about exploring the world.</p>\r\n<p>Year One pupils and their parents read the book together in class and set out to create a beautiful rock-fish art project. The pupils/parents gathered under the common area and began painting their rock-fish.</p>\r\n<p>The parents and their wards enjoyed the time together, painting vibrant colorful fish to add to the class pond. It was the perfect way to remind each and every one of us that, \"there\'s only one you in this great big world.\"</p>\r\n<p>The project was part of the Unit of Inquiry-WHO WE ARE. The central idea focused on character, ability, interest, and how it informs our learning and growth. The lines of Inquiry were centered around physical, social, and emotional characteristics, including similarities and differences between ourselves and others, personal abilities and interests. The pupils were able to share their thoughts about friendships and their own life experiences.</p>','In the book There\'s Only One You, Adri\'s mama and papa share some of the wisdom they have gained through the years with their eager son. Their words, simple and powerful, are meant to comfort and guide him as he goes abo...','2015-04-08 16:46:23','2015-04-08 16:46:23','news','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','2015-03-24 00:00:00');
