/*!40000 ALTER TABLE `people` DISABLE KEYS */;
INSERT INTO `people` VALUES (1,'Fatma','Odaymat','Principal','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/pages/dr-odaymat.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Fatma Odaymat is a Medical Doctor and Public Health Practitioner by profession, with extensive experience in managing projects and programmes dealing with women and children. For more than 15 years she has been involved in developing and managing educational and health programmes for children of all ages, including children suffering from the \'Worst Forms of Child Labour\' and \'Children Affected by Armed Conflict\' in Africa and in the Middle East. As a United Nations Officer and a consultant for many international organizations around the world she was involved in developing and managing Early Childhood Development programmes, building and/or rehabilitating schools, providing capacity building for teachers and school administrators, and working with governments on the ratification of educational and protection policies. She brings that huge resource of global experience to ARIS. She works hard to ensure that students enjoy the highest standards in international education, with a focus on international-mindedness and community service.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Under her leadership, ARIS has been approved as a Cambridge International School and is currently a Candidate School for the International Baccalaureate Primary Years and Diploma Programmes.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Dr Fatma believes that education, health and protection should be key components of every school and cannot be separated. With everyone in ARIS she strives to make sure that every student has the best possible opportunities for success; from a healthy start, excellence in educational provision and protection from harm, in a community which cares deeply about the wellbeing of every individual.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">She loves to read, sing and dance along with her three children who also attend the school.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Administration','SMT','2015-02-21 15:44:03','2015-03-10 16:06:25','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','Dr',1,'fatma-odaymat'),(3,'Larry','Aidoo','PE Coordinator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-025.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Larry Aidoo is a graduate teacher from the University of Education, Winneba, with a specialization in Physical Education and Sports. He has had seven years of teaching experience in public and international schools and is the Coordinator for the Primary and Secondary schools&rsquo; PE and Sports.</p>\r\n<p>He organises matches/competitions and serves as the Athletics and Basketball coach. Larry&rsquo;s teaching philosophy entails a strong belief that students learn through play; as youngsters play they enhance their knowledge, acquire new and improve existing skills. Introducing aspects of games and sports to young learners enhances their abilities and enriches their aspirations, both sporting and academic.</p>\r\n<p>The PE and Sports programmes aim to see students exploring higher tactical skills to generate an environment of sportsmanship and general well-being.</p>','Faculty','Primary, CAS','2015-02-21 19:46:02','2015-03-12 09:46:43','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'larry-aidoo'),(4,'Cindy-Fatima','Benshab','French Coordinator','<p>Cindy is an enthusiastic and passionate teacher at Al-Rayan International School. She joined it in 2012 and started as a French teacher to become the French Coordinator and teacher of secondary school. She holds two Bachelors&rsquo; degrees: one in languages, literature and foreign civilizations and one in linguistic studies from Paris Diderot University. She has also gained an IT management Diploma.</p>\r\n<p>Cindy is French and loves everything that has to do with French; the language itself, the culture and the food (of course). When she is teaching about France, she cannot help but make her students travel with their imagination and visit the monuments or eat a &lsquo;macaron&rsquo; at Ladur&eacute;e (French Bakery).</p>\r\n<p>When she is not teaching she loves going out with her friends, playing with her pets and shopping.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, MFL','2015-02-21 21:32:05','2015-03-10 16:39:38','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'cindy-fatima-benshab'),(5,'Mansur','Abubakar','Physics Teacher','<p>Mansur Abubakar is an experienced teacher, who is able to establish and communicate clear objectives for all learning activities and develop high quality schemes of work and lesson plans for pupils. Combining these core competencies, and CIE training for teaching and marking IGCSE Mathematics and Physics, have made him an excellent educator.</p>\r\n<p>Mansur has been a Physics teacher since September 2005 in different countries. He earned his Bachelor of Science degree in Mathematics/Physics in 2004 and a Masters in 2013. He has a long and successful experience in teaching, as well as conducting research in the field of education.</p>\r\n<p>With his previous employer, where he worked for five years, he was renowned for being able to motivate, mobilize, and coach his students to achieve the highest academic levels. He taught the best CIE Mathematics students in 2013 and 2014, with total marks of 97% and 98% respectively. He can easily work with others in a professional manner while sharing a common goal. He also considers himself to be someone whose strengths include cultural sensitivity and an ability, in a multicultural setting, to build rapport with a diverse workforce.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Science','2015-02-21 21:34:21','2015-03-10 16:12:57','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'mansur-abubakar'),(6,'Edward','Appiah','Lab Technician','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-010.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Edward Appiah is the Secondary School&rsquo;s Lab&nbsp;Technician. He was born in Accra in May 1989 and attended Accra High School, where he excelled as a student.</p>\r\n<p>Edward received a Higher National Diploma (HND) in Laboratory Technology in August 2013, while studying at the Accra Polytechnic.</p>\r\n<p>Undertaking his national service at the Ghana Atomic Energy Commission, from September 2013 to August 2014, he took part in industrial research and gained experience in data collection and sample analysis.</p>\r\n<p>For his hobbies Edward likes to watch sci-fi movies, listen to music and read books.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Science','2015-02-21 21:37:45','2015-03-25 22:44:48','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','',0,'edward-appiah'),(7,'Majida','Beiruti','RE Coordinator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-003.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Since 2005, Majida Beiruti has been the Religious Education teacher and coordinator at ARIS. She became an Arabic as a Foreign Language (AFL) teacher for the Secondary level students in 2013.</p>\r\n<p>Majida was part of the ARIS curriculum committee for several years and played a major role in organizing and managing the daily assemblies as well. She taught PSHE for more than 7 years, moral education (through drama) for more than eight years, and has been chosen as Teacher of the Year on two occasions.</p>\r\n<p>Heading the Daawah Committee women&rsquo;s section for four years, for 13 years she has also been an active member with the Ghana Society for Islamic Education and Reformation (GSIER). Majida always challenges herself into being constructive and innovative. One thing about her, is that one cannot see her in the morning without her mug of coffee and throughout the day without her smile.</p>\r\n<p>When she is free, she likes to read, to watch movies and cook.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, RE','2015-02-21 21:43:51','2015-03-11 14:04:12','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'majida-beiruti'),(8,'Stephen','Bobila','Maths Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-002.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Stephen Bobila gained admission to the University of Ghana, Legon, to read for a Bachelor of Arts degree, combining Mathematics, Computer Science, Economics and Statistics. He graduated in Mathematics with Statistics.</p>\r\n<p>After graduation, he was recruited by the university&rsquo;s Head of Mathematics Department to fulfil the National Service requirement with the department, lecturing Level 200 students and conducting tutorials with Level 100 and 300 students.</p>\r\n<p>In 2013 he joined ARIS, where he is currently teaching Extended and Additional Mathematics for the International General Certificate of Secondary Education (IGCSE).</p>\r\n<p>One of his favourite quotes is by Shakuntala Devi: &ldquo;Without mathematics, there&rsquo;s nothing you can do. Everything around you is mathematics. Everything around you is numbers.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>Stephen believes that mathematics is not just about finding the value of &ldquo;&ldquo;in the classroom context, but also involves applying how you obtained the &ldquo;&ldquo;value to your everyday activities and in solving everyday problems.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Maths','2015-02-21 21:47:49','2015-03-11 13:55:24','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'stephen-bobila'),(9,'Manelle','Boudjema','Arabic Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-018.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Mrs Manelle Boudjema was born in Algeria. A teacher of Arabic, she has a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Clinical Psychology from Mentouri University of Constantine, Algeria, from which she graduated in 2000.</p>\r\n<p>Manelle is married with two children. She likes reading, and is fascinated by news, current affairs and world events. She has been attracted to the teaching profession since she was young and, like her father, has always aspired to be a teacher.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, MFL','2015-02-21 21:53:06','2015-03-10 16:41:01','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'manelle-boudjema'),(10,'Kobena','Brew','Head of Humanities, TOK Coordinator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-012.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Born in the mid 80&rsquo;s to a Ghanaian musician/cultural ambassador and a British nurse, Kobena Brew started his primary education in the Morning Star School in Accra, where he received his Basic Education Certificate.</p>\r\n<p>He proceeded to gain his Senior High School Certificate at the Mfantsipim School, where he was elected a member of the school prefectural board in his final year. He then moved to the UK where he gained admission into Wiltshire College, Trowbridge, followed by Bournemouth University, where he attained his Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Business and Management. He went on to work for Tesco Stores as a Customer Service manager in Trowbridge, and later at Greystoke Properties in London as a Site Supervisor.</p>\r\n<p>His passion for football earned him a position as a &lsquo;Centre forward&rsquo; for Trowbridge Athletic FC where an unfortunate injury helped him discover a passion for teaching. He currently teaches IGCSE Economics, Enterprise and Business Studies and is the Head of the Humanities and Social Sciences Department.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, TOK','2015-02-21 21:56:23','2015-03-11 13:58:32','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'kobena-brew'),(11,'John','Kekeli Letsu','Chemistry Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-011.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>With a degree in Chemical Engineering from the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST), John Kekeli Letsu teaches Chemistry in the Secondary School Science Department.</p>\r\n<p>Prior to teaching, he gained over three years&rsquo; industrial experience with The Council for Scientific and Industrial Research (CSIR), the United Nations Industrial Development Organisation (UNIDO, Ghana) and lastly the German Technical Cooperation (Gtz) as a Research Assistant.</p>\r\n<p>He loves young people and derives great joy and fulfilment from helping students, especially weaker ones, achieve academic excellence in the sciences.</p>\r\n<p>Kekeli, as he is popularly called, is single and lives in Batsona, off the Spintex Road.</p>\r\n<p>He enjoys listening to classical music and hymns. As leisure activities, he plays tennis and watches movies.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Science','2015-02-21 22:00:02','2015-03-10 16:54:04','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'john-kekeli-letsu'),(12,'Boudour','Obeid','Arabic Coordinator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-004.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Boudour Obeid is the Arabic Programme Coordinator. Born and raised in Lebanon, she describes herself as a passionate educator with a special connection to the Arabic language. She is deeply committed to ensuring every student acquires close knowledge of the language. Spending many hours researching new advances and pedagogical methods, she explores Arabic materials used in other parts of the world for possible introduction to the ARIS classroom. She is very enthusiastic about encouraging students to incorporate Arabic into their daily lives, because only in this way will they learn to appreciate the true value of familiarity with the language and fluent proficiency in its use.</p>\r\n<p>Boudour enjoys reading and undertaking online research into education to add to her immeasurable collection of books and articles. Her daily routine is never complete without her morning cup of coffee while listening to the music of the famous Lebanese legend Fairuz.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, MFL','2015-02-21 22:05:08','2015-03-10 17:00:15','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',4,'boudour-obeid'),(13,'Frederick','Oppong-Boadi','Humanities Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-007.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Frederick Oppong-Boadi has a degree in Geography and Development from the Kwame Nkrumah University of Science and Technology (KNUST). He recently completed a Post Graduate Diploma in Education (PGDE) from the University of Education, Winneba.</p>\r\n<p>Fred (as he prefers) started his teaching in a local primary school in 2003 but left two years later to attend college. After working as a forestry officer for a large multinational mining corporation in Obuasi for two years, he changed career and started teaching full time in an inclusive school in 2010. Fred joined ARIS Secondary School in 2014 to teach Geography and History to Years 7 and 9, and has since trained to teach Humanities in the IB Diploma Programme. He has a huge passion for providing fun and enjoyable learning for his students.</p>\r\n<p>Fred is very proud to be part of the ARIS faculty and feels privileged to have the opportunity to work with such a diverse range of happy, hardworking and talented students. In his spare time you\'ll find him up a mountain, on a football pitch, in the gym, cooking...you get the general idea!</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Humanities','2015-02-21 22:07:52','2015-03-10 17:00:41','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'frederick-oppong-boadi'),(14,'Ali Abubakar','Siddik','Biology Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-017.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Ali Abubakar Siddik graduated from the University of Professional Studies, Legon. Having given much thought to the career directions he might take, he chose to apply to ARIS because it promised the best environment for his professional development. Ali has now been working as a teacher in the ARIS Science Department since October 2010. He entered the field because he has the passion and gift for not only teaching students but also for inspiring them, and guiding them into becoming productive citizens who have a love for learning.</p>\r\n<p>Ali is very patient and loves the excitement of being able to incorporate into his teaching diverse types of resources (such as books, digital media, music, art and movies) and bringing different experiences into the classroom. These experiences become part of the lives of some special people, ie ARIS students. Ali believes that being a facilitator in that process is a privilege that teachers enjoy much more than people in other walks of life.</p>\r\n<p>As a lifelong learner, Ali wishes to further his education, not only for the knowledge that he will gain from new courses, but also for the experience that life has to offer. During his four years at ARIS he has participated in Professional Development courses and other forms of training. These activities mean that he has to be confident, approachable, polite, reflective and an inquirer. Ali feels these are characteristics that will enable him to get involved with student life at any school in which he may work. Ambitions are to participate in conferences, in volunteer work both local and abroad, Webinars, INSETs and so on, thereby to enrich his experience. He feels confident he is on the right path.</p>\r\n<p>For recreation, Ali loves travelling, playing football and spending time with family and friends.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Science','2015-02-21 22:10:05','2015-03-11 14:36:53','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'ali-abubakar-siddik'),(15,'Dorinda','Tham','English and Global Perspectives Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-022.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>With four years in the classroom and a passion for inspiring children, Dorinda Tham teaches English Language and IGCSE Global Perspectives. It is extremely rewarding, she feels, to see how confident and enthusiastic students become when one can make them realize what they cannot see in themselves.</p>\r\n<p>Dorinda believes that learning should not just be about academics and scholarship but is also about developing and harnessing creativity, self-confidence and a sense of purpose. One of her favorite quotes is by Barbara Januszkiewicz: &ldquo;Creative thinking inspires ideas. Ideas inspire change.&rdquo; Dorinda believes that the moment teachers create the right learning environment to spark curiosity and self-confidence, they are half-way to developing creative thinkers; students who desire to make a difference no matter how small.</p>\r\n<p>On the last day of school, she can be found on the football field tackling the ball for her team.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, English and Humanities','2015-02-21 22:12:40','2015-03-10 17:09:39','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'dorinda-tham'),(16,'Juliana','Mensah','Head of Science','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-001.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Juliana Mensah graduated from the University of Cape Coast with B.Sc. degree majoring in Physics / Chemistry and with a minor in Mathematics.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">She subsequently worked with the Physics Department at the University of Ghana and initiated the review of the Level 101 Physics practical manuals. She later joined the staff at Ghana International School, teaching the Cambridge Chemistry curriculum to Lower and Upper Secondary students.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>She was the author of the Year 7 Chemistry practical manual. For organizing the World Year of Physics 2005 contest, she won the Gold Medal award from UNESCO.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Juliana is a member of the Institute of Physics and a pioneer for the &lsquo;Science on Wheels&rsquo; project for rural communities in Ghana.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Currently the IGCSE Coordinator and Head of Science in the Secondary School, Juliana teaches IGCSE Triple Science and Coordinated Sciences to Year 10 and 11 students.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Her work is guided by her belief that Science should be personally relevant and that, to be useful, it should address the challenges faced by society.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">She enjoys cooking when she has to share with guests.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Science','2015-02-21 22:25:25','2015-03-10 16:58:52','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'juliana-mensah'),(17,'Samuel','Bonney','Head of Arts','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-005.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Samuel Bonney holds a degree in Visual Art Education from the University of Education in Winneba. Although he has in the past studied and hugely enjoyed science subjects, his passion for Creative Arts finally proved irresistible, so he committed to the Visual Arts as his mainstay, his livelihood and his vocation. Samuel has also qualified in the fields of Fine Art and Journalistic Writing. Most recently, he has gained a Certificate of Completion in a Visual Arts course (Category 1) in the IB Diploma Programme.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Samuel is a member of the Artists Network University, an online art class and workshop for artists. With 31 years of work experience, of which 16 have been in teaching at various levels of art education, he has engaged himself in commissioned works, such as the statues of the Big Six, the two statues in the forecourt of Akuafo Hall (otherwise referred to as the Hall of Excellence), University of Ghana, some portrait paintings of the immediate past Speaker of Parliament, Her Excellency Joyce Bamford Addo, four paintings in the Paediatrics surgical ward at Korle-Bu Teaching Hospital, and a host of other assignments. Currently he has in his custody a life size statue of His Excellency Mr Kofi Annan, the erstwhile UN Secretary General. [Editor&rsquo;s note: Is Mr Annan aware of this?]</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">At any time, on any day, Bonney will never decline boiled slices of yam and a palatable groundnut soup, his favourite dish. He loves music and dancing Hip-life numbers and Pop/Rock music from Celine Dion.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s make the world beautiful with a touch of colour!&rdquo; he urges.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Arts','2015-02-21 22:26:02','2015-03-11 15:33:04','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'samuel-bonney'),(18,'Andrews','Adjei','Art Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-006.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Andrews Adjei is a Visual Artist with a passionate interest in textiles and graphic design. He uses various art media and tools to express himself and his visual ideas. Having also trained as a Graphic Communication artist, he has acquired specialised skills in digital media art such as CorelDRAW (a vector graphics editor) and Adobe Photoshop. Open-minded, and with a natural flair for painting and drawing, Andy has eight years of experience with palette and brush, including four years in the print industry and four years in the classroom as a support teacher.</p>\r\n<p>With other accomplished artists, Andy has embarked on a number of projects both nationally and privately. The National Population Council, the Fisheries Commission of Ghana, and the Honourable Ekow Spio Gabbrah (the current Minister of Trade and Industry) respectively have benefitted from his talents.</p>\r\n<p>Andy obtained his professional Diploma in Visual Art from the Ghanatta College of Art and Design, and a certificate in Graphic Designing from the Professional Designing Academy, Accra. He is also a member of the Artist Network University, which provides online art classes and workshops.<br />He enjoys a country music and reads almost anything, provided it is educative and informative. <br />Andy lives by the dictum that &lsquo;The world is like an empty shell that the artist must fill.&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Art','2015-02-21 22:26:54','2015-03-11 13:31:09','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'andrews-adjei'),(19,'Trevor','Trumper','Head of Secondary','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-008.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Before resuming his education, Trevor Trumper was almost a Chartered Accountant in the City. It was a road not taken. A change of direction led to his becoming a stonecutter in a granite quarry and a self-sufficient lifestyle, raising cattle, sheep, poultry and market garden products as a crofter in the Scottish Highlands. One mountain blizzard too many drove him to teacher training in English Literature, Educational Psychology and Philosophy.</p>\r\n<p>Since graduating, his work has taken him to schools from Australia to Zambia, from Beijing to Windhoek (and several places in between). His career in international education includes seven years with the IB Curriculum and Assessment Centre, responsible for Economics, Philosophy, the Arts and Theory of Knowledge, and five years as the IB Diploma Programme Manager, with worldwide responsibility for curriculum development.</p>\r\n<p>His more energetic passions include fast motorcycles and sub-aqua diving. He hopes, like Candide, he will one day tend his potager in France.</p>','Administration','SMT','2015-02-21 22:28:23','2015-03-10 16:08:17','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',3,'trevor-trumper'),(20,'Reina','Mereby Hamoui','Administrator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-009.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Reina Mereby Hamoui launched her professional dedication with college degrees, a BA in Marketing from the Hariri Canadian University (Lebanon), and an IEMBA in International Business from the Paris Graduate School of Management (France).<br /> <br />Throughout her professional embargo, she has ventured into several fields and industries. Her experience ranges from Banking, Marketing, Sales and Management. She has tested many waters from the Global Market Department (HSBC - Beirut), the Renegade Marketing Agency (Dentsu &ndash; NYC), to the Sales Department (Silver Star Auto Ltd. &ndash; Accra).<br /> <br />Reina has been with ARIS since 2013, where she has been a major influence in the many administrative fields at the school, ranging from Human Resourcing, Project Management, Procurement, Marketing, Event Organization and Corporate Identity Reestablishment.<br /> <br />She now holds the position of HR Manager and Administrator, where she works with full dedication towards excellence in her duties and the future of this esteemed institution.</p>','Administration','SMT','2015-02-21 22:31:19','2015-03-17 20:35:28','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','',7,'reina-mereby-hamoui'),(21,'Daniel','Amoako-Asante','ICT Coordinator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-013.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">As a young boy, Daniel Amoako-Asante was fascinated by gadgets and spent most of his spare time taking them apart, just to understand their mechanisms and find out how they worked.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">This set the theme for his quest to become a technocrat, which in turn led to him enrolling at university to study Wood Technology, Building Technology and Computer Engineering.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Currently he holds a BSc. in Computer Engineering from KNUST, Kumasi, and two Diplomas, one in Education and one in Building Technology.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">He joined Team ARIS in 2013 as the Information and Communication Technology (ICT) Coordinator / Teacher and is relentlessly working to guide both teachers and students to use today&rsquo;s digital tools to prepare for tomorrow&rsquo;s world.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Having taught ICT as a subject for over 11 years, Daniel has learned to optimise the full potential of today&rsquo;s technology in order to get the very best out of his students, whom he regards almost as his brothers and sisters.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">His favourite quotes include Andrew Heller&rsquo;s &ldquo;Technology is like fish. The longer it stays on the shelf, the less desirable it becomes.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">When he is not working, he cooks, plays or watches football, or might be found on a roof, tracking FTA satellite TV channels.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, ICT','2015-02-22 12:46:17','2015-03-11 13:45:40','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'daniel-amoako-asante'),(22,'Benjamin','Tee-Sowah','ICT Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-014.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Benjamin Tee-Sowah (Mr Tee as he likes to be called) is a young, vibrant man who loves technology and is always keen to impart whatever he has discovered in the hi-tech world. Colleagues and students alike are privileged with his enthusiasm, patience and expertise.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">His passion for gadgets and technology led him to tertiary education with NIIT (now BlueCrest College in Cola Street), where he acquired an Honours Diploma in Networking Engineering. Other certificates gained were as an NIIT Certified PC Technician, in Microsoft Office Proficiency and a Young Searchers League Bible Searching Certificate. He later pursued a one-year top-up degree programme with The Open University, UK, through which he acquired a Certificate in Fundamentals of Interaction Design.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">He is compelled to work in education by his philosophy that &lsquo;teaching is the recreation of a better you in another person&rsquo;. He is a self-motivated fellow who loves challenges because, to him, &lsquo;nothing is difficult; everything is a challenge&rsquo;. He is gregarious, he is friendly and jovial. He chose ICT because of a firm belief that technology is the hub from which all other subjects radiate.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">His hobbies include playing basketball, football, jockeying the discs and computer games. He writes spoken-word poetry and loves to tear down and fix gadgets of all descriptions.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, ICT','2015-02-22 12:47:22','2015-03-10 17:06:54','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'benjamin-tee-sowah'),(23,'Victoria','Budu','English Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-015.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Victoria Budu holds a degree in English and has a great insight into varying educational curricula. She however has a specialty in both the British and Cambridge educational systems.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Throughout her teaching career, she has acquired a firm knowledge of effective teaching and learning methods to equip students appropriately.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Consequently, she is endowed with an immense degree of experience, both in Ghana and in the United Kingdom. She teaches English Language at the Secondary level and has fervency for music.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Discipline and honesty are her key traits. For her, English Language is the pivot around which the entire globe revolves. Her passion for teaching her academic discipline is summed up in the words:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>&ldquo;English moves the world&rdquo;.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, English','2015-02-22 12:48:05','2015-03-10 16:41:36','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'victoria-budu'),(24,'Doris','Adu-Bekoe','Receptionist','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-016.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Staff','Secondary','2015-02-22 12:49:33','2015-03-11 15:02:18','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'doris-adu-bekoe'),(25,'Emmanuel','Forson','Head of Maths','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-019.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Emmanuel Forson is a Ghanaian who has been raised to be gentle, honest, open, specific and trustworthy. He attended the Ghana Secondary Technical School (Takoradi), majored in Botany at the University of Cape Coast and graduated cum laude. He has since had the opportunity to read various courses in Science and Mathematics, learn and teach in South Africa and United Kingdom, where his personal and professional ethics have grown and developed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Growing as a child, Anokye attended the Westridge International School at Sekondi &ndash; a school with strong educational and ethical philosophy that have remained his guiding principle in life. This foundation, together with his fundamental values and support from his family, educators and friends have encouraged him to embrace his dream of teaching children who do not have the support and nurturing they need to realise their full potential.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Anokye joined Al-Rayan International School in 2011 and has since been a teacher who young children look up to, can trust, and will go the extra mile to ensure their success. He is currently reading a certificate course in conflict management and hopes to help resolve conflicts in the educational sector using the interest based approach.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Maths','2015-02-22 12:53:27','2015-03-11 14:08:06','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'emmanuel-forson'),(26,'Katherine','Tetteh','Librarian','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-020.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Katherine Tetteh attended Eastern Washington University, where in 2008 she earned a Bachelor\'s degree in Social Work. Following graduation, she worked with multiple charities and non-profit organisations, including two terms with AmeriCorps in Spokane, Washington State, and one term with Community Service Volunteers in St. Neots, England, UK. Using her education award earnings from AmeriCorps, Katherine enrolled at Spokane Falls Community College and graduated with a degree in Business Technology as an administrative assistant.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In 2014, Katie was working for a communications firm, Let It Shine LLC. and SCAN, a non-profit organisation which facilitates visits with families in foster care. In June of that year, she married her Ghanaian husband and moved to Accra. She was quickly introduced to many communities in Ghana including her church, to Ashesi University, and now Al-Rayan International School.</p>\r\n<p>As Secondary School Librarian she is vested with the huge task of creating a state-of the-art Library/Multimedia Centre, not only meeting the needs of ARIS students in the twenty-first century learning environment and its concomitant digital technologies, but by working from within the teaching faculty, widening horizons and raising expectations of future possibilities.</p>\r\n<p>Katie enjoys creating a space where relevant and important information is readily accessible. She wants the Library/Multimedia Centre to be dynamic; a place where learning is exciting and engaging, but also a place conducive, when appropriate, to calmness and scholarly reflection.</p>\r\n<p>Katie enjoys cooking food, especially baking. She values in-depth conversations as well as socialising in groups. She also enjoys movies and exercising. She has a large personal audiobook library and frequently listens to podcasts. She feels her transition to Ghana has been enriching, because even though there are challenges in the developing world, the opportunities and adventures outweigh them.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\'Our deepest fear is not that we\'re inadequate. Our deepest fear is that we are powerful beyond measure. It is our Light, not our Darkness, that frightens us beyond measure.\' <em>Marianne Williamson</em></p>','Faculty','Secondary, Library','2015-02-22 12:56:09','2015-03-11 14:53:31','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'katherine-tetteh'),(28,'Ida','Allotey-Brown','SEN and EAL Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-023.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Ida is an honest, organised, well-disciplined and reliable person who has a passion for nurturing students. She teaches English as an Additional Language (EAL) to students new to English Language in addition to identifying and assisting students who have specific learning difficulties or challenges (SEN).</p>\r\n<p>Prior to being in the educational sector, Ida acquired several years of experience working with people in different sectors including Insurance Brokerage, Ghana Water Company Limited and in the Accounts Department of Ghana Commercial Bank (GCB).</p>\r\n<p>Ida joined Al-Rayan International School (ARIS) in 2011 and believes that a teacher is not just a guide, but a friend who helps with the learning process and that&rsquo;s why she is in ARIS. A day in her life is not complete till she has an interaction with people who are hearing impaired. Her hobbies include trying new recipes, watching movies and travelling.</p>\r\n<p>She says, &ldquo;Over the years, I have enjoyed seeing the students outperform their own expectations and such successes have brought me a great deal of satisfaction and confidence.&rdquo; </p>','Faculty','SEN, EAL','2015-02-22 17:47:35','2015-04-08 10:50:46','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','',0,'ida-allotey-brown'),(29,'Dhalia','Sabeh','Counsellor, CAS Coordinator','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-024.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Dhalia Sabeh holds a Bachelor&rsquo;s Degree in Business and Finance in addition to extensive experience and certification as a Clinical Counselor from the state of California.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Dhalia was a member of the Clinical Counselor&rsquo;s Association and has travelled to over thirty countries engaging in Service for Humanity. She is dedicated to helping others improve their lives through service and experiential learning, developing insight, and change. <br /> <br /> Dhalia is a married mother of two children. She has over fifteen years&rsquo; experience as an educator, mental health counselor and philanthropist, and she interacts with individuals and families of all types in California, Ghana and throughout the world. Early in her counseling and service learning career, Dhalia worked as a counselor in California, but now lives in Accra where she coordinates the personal counseling, career guidance, and PSHE and CAS programmes in ARIS. As a therapist, she is able to integrate her knowledge of education and mental health issues to help students and families problem-solve, overcome personal issues, and work toward positive home and school experiences. <br /> <br /> Dhalia also counsels individually with adults who are experiencing life transitions, mood disorders, grief and loss, or psychological and spiritual problems. Her clients include those who wish to improve their personal relationships, communication, and/or life skills.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, CAS, Counselling','2015-02-22 17:49:12','2015-03-11 14:35:28','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',5,'dhalia-sabeh'),(30,'Dania','Sadek','Head of Primary','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-026.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Dania Sadek holds a Bachelor of Science Degree (Honours) in Biology from the Lebanese American University. Despite the high achievement she attained to enable her entry into the medical school, she diverted her career into education. She began her teaching career as a Biology Teacher at the Ghana Lebanon Islamic Senior Secondary School in January, 2001. Then in September, 2006 Dania joined ARIS as a Year 3 teacher, then in the years to follow, she taught in Years 4, 5 and 6. Dania also taught Science in Years 7, 8 and 9 innovating her pupils to develop a passion for biology, from observing their cheek cells under a microscope to classifying the animals, like the hen they had brought from home.</p>\r\n<p><br />Having acquired an in depth understanding of the strategies and methodologies of the British National Curriculum, Dania was made the Literacy Coordinator, then the Assessment Coordinator till she eventually held the post of Key Stage two coordinator in 2011. Throughout her years at ARIS, Dania continued to participate in CIE workshops at the British Council, and online. In addition, she is currently undergoing IB professional development trainings in-school, online and abroad<br />In September 2014, she was made the Head of Primary, and Acting PYP coordinator.</p>','Administration','SMT','2015-02-22 17:50:05','2015-03-17 21:47:25','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','',2,'dania-sadek'),(31,'Symplice','Athodjinou','IT Officer','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-027.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Staff','IT Department','2015-02-22 17:51:07','2015-03-11 15:05:41','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'symplice-athodjinou'),(32,'Francis','Gaetan','French Primary Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-028.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 17:51:55','2015-03-10 16:50:56','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'francis-gaetan'),(33,'Nana Akua','Ampong','Administrative Assistant','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-029.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Staff','Primary','2015-02-22 17:53:11','2015-03-11 15:04:33','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'nana-akua-ampong'),(34,'Leiticia','Boateng','Primary Secretary','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-030.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Staff','Administrative Assistant','2015-02-22 17:55:20','2015-03-11 15:09:54','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'leiticia-boateng'),(35,'Anamika','Sinha','Hindi Primary Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-031.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 17:56:58','2015-03-10 17:05:11','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'anamika-sinha'),(36,'Dionne','Puplampu','SEN Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-032.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 17:58:05','2015-03-10 17:02:50','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'dionne-puplampu'),(37,'Ayorkor','Dua','Primary Class Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-033.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Ayorkor Dua gained admission into Wilson College, Pennsylvania, USA and graduated with a Bachelors&rsquo; Degree in Elementary Education. After graduation, she moved back to Ghana and joined the ARIS family in August 2014. She is currently the Year 5 teacher for the International Baccalaureate Primary Years Program (IB PYP).</p>\r\n<p>In her spare time, she likes to read, go to the beach and socialise with family and friends. One of her favourite quotes about teaching is, &ldquo;tell me and I&rsquo;ll forget, teach me and I&rsquo;ll remember, involve me and I&rsquo;ll learn!&rdquo; by Benjamin Franklin.</p>\r\n<p>She looks forward to more exciting school years with the wonderful ARIS family.</p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 17:58:49','2015-03-10 16:43:21','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'ayorkor-dua'),(39,'Phyllis','Nkansah','EAL Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-036.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary, EAL','2015-02-22 18:00:50','2015-03-28 00:37:10','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Ms.',0,'phyllis-nkansah'),(40,'Richard','Gavor','Primary Class Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-037.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 18:02:42','2015-03-10 16:51:11','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'richard-gavor'),(41,'Christopher Yaw','Dotse','Library Assistant','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-039.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Christopher Dotse attended Ho Polytechnic where he studied Accounting. He did his Industrial attachments with the Cash Office at the University Of Ghana Hospital, Legon. He also attended a Professional Career Enhancement Seminar organized by the School Of Business and Management Studies (SOBAMS) in Ho Polytechnic.</p>\r\n<p>After completion, he continued with his National Service and was posted to Mercy Islamic Junior High School where he taught Religious and Moral Education and Social Studies.</p>\r\n<p>He joined Al-Rayan International School in 2009. He is also a member of the Institute Of Chartered Accountants &ndash; Ghana (ICA-GH).<br />His hobbies are acting, drawing and listening to music. His favourite motivational quote is &lsquo;&rsquo;If it must be enjoyed, then it must be done. And if it must be done, then it must be done well. If it is done well, it is enjoyed well.&rdquo;</p>','Faculty','Primary, Library','2015-02-22 18:04:36','2015-04-08 14:58:28','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','',0,'christopher-yaw-dotse'),(42,'Vincentia','Kpodo','Primary Class Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-040.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 18:05:55','2015-03-10 16:54:29','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'vincentia-kpodo'),(45,'Rouba','Maatouk','Primary Class Teacher','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-043.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Rouba George Mattouk earned a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Early Childhood Education and Master&rsquo;s degree in Educational Leadership at the School Management from Notre Dame University, Zouk Mosbeh.</p>\r\n<p>Her career began in 2010 as an Elementary Science Teacher and substitute English teacher in Jesus and Mary School, Rabieh Lebanon. In 2013, she worked in St Charbel International School as an English Teacher.</p>\r\n<p>Her Favourite quote is &ldquo;Teachers who love teaching teach children to love learning.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>She believes that teaching is a passion and a natural gift in which training can improve but cannot make one a teacher. Effective teachers work from the heart to empower students and help them become independent learners. This is what Education is all about.</p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 18:08:44','2015-04-08 14:45:17','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','',0,'rouba-maatouk'),(46,'Dominic','Dzineku','IT Support Officer','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-044.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Dominic Dzineku gained admission into Ho Polytechnic in Volta Region, to read Marketing. He graduated with a Higher National Diploma in Marketing.</p>\r\n<p>After graduation, he was recruited by Ghana Education Service to fulfill the National Service requirement at Methodist Junior High School in Ho, where he taught Core Mathematics and Core Science to Junior High School students.</p>\r\n<p>He then gained admission into IPMC to complete a Diploma in Hardware, Network Engineering and attained a Microsoft Certified Systems Engineering certificate.</p>\r\n<p>In 2011, he joined ARIS and taught ICT at primary and IGCSE level for three years. He is currently the IT Technical Support Officer in the ARIS Primary School.</p>','Staff','IT Department','2015-02-22 18:09:26','2015-04-08 11:51:18','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','',0,'dominic-dzineku'),(47,'Maya','Hamedi','ICT Primary Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-045.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Maya Hamedi graduated with distinction from the University of Balamand with a BS degree in Information Systems. During her undergraduate studies, she maintained a place on the Dean\'s Honor List, and received the Faculty of Sciences Excellence Award for best final project, where she created an online library system using PHP and MySql. <br /> <br />After that, Maya was granted a full graduate scholarship at the Lebanese American University (LAU) where she got and MS degree in Computer Science and specialized in Software Engineering.<br /> <br />Maya pursed a two year teaching career in Lebanon before moving to Ghana: she became a part time instructor at LAU, teaching the IT Fundamentals and Computer Applications course to junior students, and worked at Rawdat Al Fayhaa\' School giving Computing classes to young children in primary. <br /> <br />During her free time, Maya loves to bake, sew, cross stitch, and take care of her little garden.</p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 18:10:24','2015-03-10 16:51:32','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'maya-hamedi'),(48,'Evon','Maatouk','Primary Class Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-046.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 18:11:04','2015-03-10 16:58:27','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'evon-maatouk'),(49,'Eugenia','Afawubo','Primary Class Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-047.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Eugenia Afawubo obtained her degree from the University of Ghana, Legon. She read a Bachelor of Arts degree in English, Linguistic and History and graduated in English and History.</p>\r\n<p>She went on to do her National Service at Ghana International School where she was exposed to the British National Curriculum. She worked in class 4 as a Teaching Assistant. With the exposure Eugenia had at GIS she realized she had a calling for teaching.</p>\r\n<p>In 2013 she joined the ARIS family and is currently teaching year 2B.</p>\r\n<p>One of her best quotes is &lsquo;A man who asks is a fool for five minutes. A man who never asks is a fool for life&rsquo;. Eugenia also believes life is about finding your calling and fulfilling it.</p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-22 18:11:43','2015-04-08 10:41:54','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','',0,'eugenia-afawubo'),(50,'Gloria','Appiah','Music Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-048.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Gloria Appiah completed a Bachelor of Fine Arts degree at the University of Ghana and then served as a teaching assistant in the university&rsquo;s Music Department. For the first two years she was teaching students on a one-to-one basis. Unabashedly, she admits that she &lsquo;fell in love with educating the young people I met during those one-to-one sessions&rsquo;.</p>\r\n<p>Currently teaching Music on a part-time basis in both the Primary and Secondary Schools, she considers herself fortunate to work with children most days of the week. She is always eager to take their learning forward with thought-provoking topics and working on the earliest stages of getting students prepared for the eventual transition to university.</p>\r\n<p>&lsquo;Teaching is exciting,&rsquo; she says, &lsquo;no two days are the same!&rsquo; She particularly enjoys teaching lessons that allow students to be creative, and always seeks to provide stimulating and engaging learning opportunities. She has, of course, a passion for music. Her favourite aspect of the job is seeing the children develop in their musical life.</p>\r\n<p>&lsquo;I love seeing children singing and playing instruments with a smile on their face, as I believe that when children are comfortable in their surroundings, and enjoying what they&rsquo;re doing, they progress at a much quicker pace.&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>Away from the classroom she is passionate about singing. Her pastimes and recreational activities include travelling, films, walking, reading, dancing, cooking and visiting friends and family.</p>','Faculty','Primary, Secondary, Arts','2015-02-22 18:12:27','2015-03-18 08:21:06','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'gloria-appiah'),(51,'Samira','Keni Asare','Primary Class Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-050.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-23 19:10:27','2015-03-11 13:52:12','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'samira-keni-asare'),(54,'Nana Asantewa','Adutwum','Primary Class Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-053.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Nana Asantewaa Adutwum gained admission into the University Of Cape Coast, to pursue a Bachelor of Arts degree in Population and Family Life.</p>\r\n<p>After graduation, she was recruited by Nsawam Government Hospital to fulfill the National Service requirement with the records department and became passionate about working with children.</p>\r\n<p>In 2011, she joined ARIS as a teaching assistant, and as a virtue of her diligence, is currently the class teacher for year one.</p>\r\n<p>One of her favourite quotes by Tom Bodett is, &ldquo;In school you are taught a lesson and then given a test, in life you are given a test that teaches you a lesson&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>She also believes, according to Conrad Hall that one is always a student, not a master. You have to keep moving forward. In addition, she believes the more you read, the more things you will know, the more you learn, the more places you will go.&rdquo;</p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-23 19:14:37','2015-04-08 10:39:02','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','',0,'nana-asantewa-adutwum'),(56,'Samuel','Asante','Art  PrimaryTeacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-055.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-23 19:15:53','2015-03-05 10:30:31','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','Mr.',0,'samuel-asante'),(57,'Safa','Beiruti','RE Primary Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-056.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-23 19:16:56','2015-03-11 14:05:41','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'safa-beiruti'),(58,'Richard','Annobil','Primary Class Teacher, Team Leader','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-057.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-23 19:17:37','2015-03-12 09:47:28','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'richard-annobil'),(59,'Janet','Kyeremeh','Foundation Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-058.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Janet Kyeremeh gained admission to the University of Cape-Coast, to read a Degree in Education, combining Special Education, and Child Psychology and graduated with a Degree in Basic Education.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">She was then recruited by the University of Ghana Basic School to fulfill the National Service requirement with the foundation department, teaching foundation stage and conducting in-service trainings for teachers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">In 2013 she joined ARIS, where she is currently teaching a reception class in the primary section.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">One of her favourite quotes is, &ldquo;The wonder of teaching is watching caterpillars become butterflies.&rdquo;(Unknown)</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Janet&rsquo;s hobbies include reading, travelling and generally staying aware of current events. She loves plants and all green things. Her favourite kids&rsquo; book is &lsquo;Where the Red Fern Grows by Wilson Rawls&rsquo;.</p>','Faculty','Foundation','2015-02-23 19:18:18','2015-03-10 16:55:01','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'janet-kyeremeh'),(60,'Maissa','Yamak','Foundation Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-060.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Foundation','2015-02-23 19:37:39','2015-03-10 17:08:47','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'maissa-yamak'),(61,'Hassana','Mensah','Foundation Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-061.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Foundation','2015-02-23 19:42:13','2015-03-10 16:59:19','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'hassana-mensah'),(63,'Ikbal','Barakeh','Foundation Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-063.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Faculty','Foundation','2015-02-23 19:43:46','2015-03-10 16:38:33','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'ikbal-barakeh'),(64,'Dayna','Toutoungi','Admissions and Communication Manager','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-064.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Dayna is beginning her fourth year at ARIS as the Admissions and Communication Manager. She has a broad background working and volunteering in American K-12 public schools administration. She has over twenty years of experience in administration and implementing school based programmes, such as M.E.S.A, Math Counts, S.T.E.M, and was a leading contributor to the Positive Behavior System (PBS) in Denver, Colorado. She was also a private business owner, contracted with government-based agencies that provided handicapped accessible transportation to people with disabilities.</p>\r\n<p>During her tenure at ARIS, she has demonstrated the ability to be an effective leader in the areas of student achievement, strategic planning, school improvement, student behaviour, and community/parent involvement. Dayna builds strong relationships with staff, students and parents. She is truly committed to enriching the lives of our students, each and every day. Dayna is a native of Southern California, but has called Ghana home for the last four years and is married with four children, three of them attending ARIS.</p>','Administration','SMT','2015-02-23 19:45:48','2015-03-13 09:55:52','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','',8,'dayna-toutoungi'),(65,'Alimatu','Sadia Ali','Administrative Assistant','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-065.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>','Staff','Administrative Assistant','2015-02-23 19:46:45','2015-03-11 15:12:57','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'alimatu-sadia-ali'),(66,'Solomon','Elloh','PE Primary Teacher','<p><img src=\"/img/uploads/people/people-066.jpg\" alt=\"\" /><br />Solomon Elloh is an industrious professional with a good balance of education and experience in physical education. He is currently responsible for physically training the students in all sporting games as well as teaching them how to dance.</p>\r\n<p>Mr. Solomon holds a graduate diploma in physical education and has worked with schools such as Glory of Zion Int. School and Glorious Child Complex School. He has worked with children from the ages of 5 and above for the past ten years and this rich experience is evident in ARIS. His task now is to mobilize students to form a team in the various sporting disciplines for upcoming competitions.</p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-02-23 19:47:11','2015-04-08 14:55:39','dtoutoungi@aris.edu.gh','',0,'solomon-elloh'),(67,'Maud','Adjanor','Foundation Teacher','<p class=\"p1\">There is nothing more gratifying than witnessing a young child learn something new, knowing that there has been a driving force behind that growth. Maud Adjanor is an inherent teacher who is passionate about how children grow. She gained admission into the University of Education, Winneba after teaching for six years in the early years. Maud holds a diploma in Early Childhood Education and has pursued various courses including child psychology, child rights, and educational philosophy just to mention a few. She is currently reading Bachelor of Arts in childhood education at the same University.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">She joined ARIS in 2010 as a teacher in the early year foundation department and has been very involved in the mammoth transformation of the department. She presently is the reception (A) class teacher. Maud trusts that child growth is one aspect of life that the world cannot do away with, and what makes the child a holistic matured being is not only the environment but the experiences and choices that should be carefully guided to help the child. Her ideas are from her inspirations, which come from the word of God.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Maud enjoys exploring in all aspects whether home or school and can create magnificent things out of zilch. Train a child the way he should go and when he grows he will not depart from it. Proverbs 22:6, \"Whoever welcomes one of these little children in my name welcomes me; and whoever welcomes me does not welcome me but the one who sent me\" according to Mark 9:37. These are verses Maud believes in. A world without teachers is lost a world.</p>','Faculty','Foundation','2015-02-27 16:35:35','2015-03-10 16:28:40','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'maud-adjanor'),(68,'Thomas','Harvey','Maths Teacher','<p class=\"p1\">Thomas S Harvey is a Ghanaian who has been trained to be gentle, honest and diligent. He attended the University of Cape Coast where he obtained his B.Ed. degree. To achieve greater insight into the field of education, he has also read various other educational courses. He has taught in many international schools in Ghana.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">As a child, Thomas attended the Extra Mural Academy at Dansoman. That school&rsquo;s motto, &lsquo;We improve and advance&rsquo;, has inspired him to become an educator to help improve and advance himself and others in knowledge.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">Thomas joined Al-Rayan International School in 2009 and has become a teacher for both Primary and Secondary school students. He is a trustworthy person who loves to work with all. He is currently working hard to become a Mathematical Financial Analyst.</p>','Faculty','Secondary, Maths','2015-03-02 20:26:35','2015-03-11 14:10:29','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'thomas-harvey'),(69,'Fida','Husseini','Financial Manager','<p>Madame Fida Husseini has been a part of ARIS from its point of conception, serving ARIS for more than ten years. She is a pioneer of ARIS administration and has held various integral positions throughout the years. She oversees a broad range of departments including budget and resource planning, business affairs, procurement, campus planning, design and construction, internal audit, and day-to-day campus operations.</p>\r\n<p>She is currently the Finance Manager and works directly with the governing board and Head of School on all financial matters. Madame Fida has made strong connections with the staff and parents that she has diligently worked with for so many years. She is a native of Lebanon but has called Ghana home for the past 26 years. She is happily married and has four children. &nbsp;</p>','Administration','SMT','2015-03-05 09:37:14','2015-03-13 09:57:21','mustapha.hamoui@gmail.com','',6,'fida-husseini'),(70,'Fusena','Mensah','Foundation Teacher','<p>This is the biography of Fusena Mensah.</p>','Faculty','Foundation','2015-03-05 09:44:48','2015-03-11 14:21:58','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'fusena-mensah'),(71,'Wendy','Owusu','Foundation Teacher','<p>This is the biography of Wendy Owusu.</p>','Faculty','Foundation','2015-03-05 09:46:05','2015-03-11 14:25:46','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'wendy-owusu'),(72,'Bader','El Osta','Arabic Coordinator','<p>This is the biography of Bader El Osta</p>','Faculty','Foundation, Primary','2015-03-05 09:57:10','2015-03-10 16:44:34','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'bader-el-osta'),(73,'Estelle','Enoh','French Foundation Teacher','<p>This is the biography&nbsp;of Estelle Enoh</p>','Faculty','Foundation','2015-03-05 10:00:54','2015-03-11 14:56:17','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'estelle-enoh'),(74,'Sidonnie Pascale','Aka','French Primary Teacher','<p>This is the biography of Sidonnie Pascale Aka</p>','Faculty','Primary','2015-03-05 10:16:17','2015-03-11 14:41:57','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'sidonnie-pascale-aka'),(75,'Osei','Baffour','English Teacher','<p>This is the bio of Osei Baffour&nbsp;</p>','Faculty','Secondary, English','2015-03-05 18:18:50','2015-03-10 16:46:58','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'osei-baffour'),(77,'William','Teifio','SEN Teacher','<p>This is the biography of William Teifio</p>','Faculty','Primary, EAL','2015-03-05 19:46:00','2015-03-11 14:50:44','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'william-teifio'),(78,'Dibuseng','Asante','IT Officer','<p>This is the biography of Dibuseng Asante.</p>','Staff','IT Department','2015-03-05 19:57:26','2015-03-11 15:07:01','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'dibuseng-asante'),(79,'Zainab','Yahya','Senior Accountant','<p>Zainab Yahya is a qualified Chartered Accountant, and has been working as an accountant with ARIS for the past five years, with over seven years cumulative experience. She is currently a full member of the Association of Chartered Certified Accountants (ACCA) in the UK and is a graduating student with a B.Sc. (Hons) in Applied Accounting at the Oxford Brookes University. <br />As an accountant, she strives for excellence in all professional endeavours. She also believes that service with excellence and integrity are core values in professional practice.<br />She enjoys sightseeing as a hobby and always likes to visit new places for an adventure.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','Staff','Finance','2015-03-05 19:58:42','2015-03-17 13:17:15','ttrumper@aris.edu.gh','',0,'zainab-yahya');
